34/* Compiler-assisted vectorization. */
35
36/* Type behaving similar to vectorized vars defined using __attribute__((vector_size(...))),
37 * basically a fixed-size bitset. We can't use the compiler type because hb_vector_t cannot
38 * guarantee alignment requirements. */
39template <typename elt_t, unsigned int byte_size>
40struct hb_vector_size_t
41{
42 elt_t& operator [] (unsigned int i) { return v[i]; }
43 const elt_t& operator [] (unsigned int i) const { return v[i]; }
44
45 void init0 ()
46 {
47 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < ARRAY_LENGTH (v); i++)
48 v[i] = 0;
49 }
50 void init1 ()
51 {
52 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < ARRAY_LENGTH (v); i++)
53 v[i] = (elt_t) -1;
54 }
55
56 template <typename Op>
57 hb_vector_size_t process (const Op& op) const
58 {
59 hb_vector_size_t r;
60 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < ARRAY_LENGTH (v); i++)
61 r.v[i] = op (v[i]);
62 return r;
63 }
64 template <typename Op>
65 hb_vector_size_t process (const Op& op, const hb_vector_size_t &o) const
66 {
67 hb_vector_size_t r;
68 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < ARRAY_LENGTH (v); i++)
69 r.v[i] = op (v[i], o.v[i]);
70 return r;
71 }
72 hb_vector_size_t operator | (const hb_vector_size_t &o) const
73 { return process (hb_bitwise_or, o); }
74 hb_vector_size_t operator & (const hb_vector_size_t &o) const
75 { return process (hb_bitwise_and, o); }
76 hb_vector_size_t operator ^ (const hb_vector_size_t &o) const
77 { return process (hb_bitwise_xor, o); }
78 hb_vector_size_t operator ~ () const
79 { return process (hb_bitwise_neg); }
80
81 hb_array_t<const elt_t> iter () const
82 { return hb_array (v); }
83
84 private:
85 static_assert (0 == byte_size % sizeof (elt_t), "");
86 elt_t v[byte_size / sizeof (elt_t)];
87};

89
90struct hb_bit_page_t
91{
92 void init0 () { v.init0 (); }
93 void init1 () { v.init1 (); }
94
95 static inline constexpr unsigned len ()
96 { return ARRAY_LENGTH_CONST (v); }
97
98 bool is_empty () const
99 {
100 return
101 + hb_iter (v)
102 | hb_none
103 ;
104 }
105 uint32_t hash () const
106 {
107 return
108 + hb_iter (v)
109 | hb_reduce ([] (uint32_t h, const elt_t &_) { return h * 31 + hb_hash (_); }, (uint32_t) 0u)
110 ;
111 }
112
113 void add (hb_codepoint_t g) { elt (g) |= mask (g); }
114 void del (hb_codepoint_t g) { elt (g) &= ~mask (g); }
115 void set (hb_codepoint_t g, bool value) { if (value) add (g); else del (g); }
116 bool get (hb_codepoint_t g) const { return elt (g) & mask (g); }
117
118 void add_range (hb_codepoint_t a, hb_codepoint_t b)
119 {
120 elt_t *la = &elt (g: a);
121 elt_t *lb = &elt (g: b);
122 if (la == lb)
123 *la |= (mask (g: b) << 1) - mask(g: a);
124 else
125 {
126 *la |= ~(mask (g: a) - 1);
127 la++;
128
129 hb_memset (s: la, c: 0xff, n: (char *) lb - (char *) la);
130
131 *lb |= ((mask (g: b) << 1) - 1);
132 }
133 }
134 void del_range (hb_codepoint_t a, hb_codepoint_t b)
135 {
136 elt_t *la = &elt (g: a);
137 elt_t *lb = &elt (g: b);
138 if (la == lb)
139 *la &= ~((mask (g: b) << 1) - mask(g: a));
140 else
141 {
142 *la &= mask (g: a) - 1;
143 la++;
144
145 hb_memset (s: la, c: 0, n: (char *) lb - (char *) la);
146
147 *lb &= ~((mask (g: b) << 1) - 1);
148 }
149 }
150 void set_range (hb_codepoint_t a, hb_codepoint_t b, bool v)
151 { if (v) add_range (a, b); else del_range (a, b); }
152
153
154 // Writes out page values to the array p. Returns the number of values
155 // written. At most size codepoints will be written.
156 unsigned int write (uint32_t base,
157 unsigned int start_value,
158 hb_codepoint_t *p,
159 unsigned int size) const
160 {
161 unsigned int start_v = start_value / ELT_BITS;
162 unsigned int start_bit = start_value & ELT_MASK;
163 unsigned int count = 0;
164 for (unsigned i = start_v; i < len () && count < size; i++)
165 {
166 elt_t bits = v[i];
167 uint32_t v_base = base | (i * ELT_BITS);
168 for (unsigned int j = start_bit; j < ELT_BITS && count < size; j++)
169 {
170 if ((elt_t(1) << j) & bits) {
171 *p++ = v_base | j;
172 count++;
173 }
174 }
175 start_bit = 0;
176 }
177 return count;
178 }
179
180 // Writes out the values NOT in this page to the array p. Returns the
181 // number of values written. At most size codepoints will be written.
182 // Returns the number of codepoints written. next_value holds the next value
183 // that should be written (if not present in this page). This is used to fill
184 // any missing value gaps between this page and the previous page, if any.
185 // next_value is updated to one more than the last value present in this page.
186 unsigned int write_inverted (uint32_t base,
187 unsigned int start_value,
188 hb_codepoint_t *p,
189 unsigned int size,
190 hb_codepoint_t *next_value) const
191 {
192 unsigned int start_v = start_value / ELT_BITS;
193 unsigned int start_bit = start_value & ELT_MASK;
194 unsigned int count = 0;
195 for (unsigned i = start_v; i < len () && count < size; i++)
196 {
197 elt_t bits = v[i];
198 uint32_t v_offset = i * ELT_BITS;
199 for (unsigned int j = start_bit; j < ELT_BITS && count < size; j++)
200 {
201 if ((elt_t(1) << j) & bits)
202 {
203 hb_codepoint_t value = base | v_offset | j;
204 // Emit all the missing values from next_value up to value - 1.
205 for (hb_codepoint_t k = *next_value; k < value && count < size; k++)
206 {
207 *p++ = k;
208 count++;
209 }
210 // Skip over this value;
211 *next_value = value + 1;
212 }
213 }
214 start_bit = 0;
215 }
216 return count;
217 }
218
219 bool is_equal (const hb_bit_page_t &other) const
220 {
221 for (unsigned i = 0; i < len (); i++)
222 if (v[i] != other.v[i])
223 return false;
224 return true;
225 }
226 bool is_subset (const hb_bit_page_t &larger_page) const
227 {
228 for (unsigned i = 0; i < len (); i++)
229 if (~larger_page.v[i] & v[i])
230 return false;
231 return true;
232 }
233
234 unsigned int get_population () const
235 {
236 return
237 + hb_iter (v)
238 | hb_reduce ([] (unsigned pop, const elt_t &_) { return pop + hb_popcount (v: _); }, 0u)
239 ;
240 }
241
242 bool next (hb_codepoint_t *codepoint) const
243 {
244 unsigned int m = (*codepoint + 1) & MASK;
245 if (!m)
246 {
247 *codepoint = INVALID;
248 return false;
249 }
250 unsigned int i = m / ELT_BITS;
251 unsigned int j = m & ELT_MASK;
252
253 const elt_t vv = v[i] & ~((elt_t (1) << j) - 1);
254 for (const elt_t *p = &vv; i < len (); p = &v[++i])
255 if (*p)
256 {
257 *codepoint = i * ELT_BITS + elt_get_min (elt: *p);
258 return true;
259 }
260
261 *codepoint = INVALID;
262 return false;
263 }
264 bool previous (hb_codepoint_t *codepoint) const
265 {
266 unsigned int m = (*codepoint - 1) & MASK;
267 if (m == MASK)
268 {
269 *codepoint = INVALID;
270 return false;
271 }
272 unsigned int i = m / ELT_BITS;
273 unsigned int j = m & ELT_MASK;
274
275 /* Fancy mask to avoid shifting by elt_t bitsize, which is undefined. */
276 const elt_t mask = j < 8 * sizeof (elt_t) - 1 ?
277 ((elt_t (1) << (j + 1)) - 1) :
278 (elt_t) -1;
279 const elt_t vv = v[i] & mask;
280 const elt_t *p = &vv;
281 while (true)
282 {
283 if (*p)
284 {
285 *codepoint = i * ELT_BITS + elt_get_max (elt: *p);
286 return true;
287 }
288 if ((int) i <= 0) break;
289 p = &v[--i];
290 }
291
292 *codepoint = INVALID;
293 return false;
294 }
295 hb_codepoint_t get_min () const
296 {
297 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < len (); i++)
298 if (v[i])
299 return i * ELT_BITS + elt_get_min (elt: v[i]);
300 return INVALID;
301 }
302 hb_codepoint_t get_max () const
303 {
304 for (int i = len () - 1; i >= 0; i--)
305 if (v[i])
306 return i * ELT_BITS + elt_get_max (elt: v[i]);
307 return 0;
308 }
309
310 static constexpr hb_codepoint_t INVALID = HB_SET_VALUE_INVALID;
311
312 typedef unsigned long long elt_t;
313 static constexpr unsigned PAGE_BITS_LOG_2 = 9; // 512 bits
314 static constexpr unsigned PAGE_BITS = 1 << PAGE_BITS_LOG_2;
315 static_assert (1 << PAGE_BITS_LOG_2 == PAGE_BITS, "");
316 static_assert ((PAGE_BITS & ((PAGE_BITS) - 1)) == 0, "");
317 static constexpr unsigned PAGE_BITMASK = PAGE_BITS - 1;
318
319 static unsigned int elt_get_min (const elt_t &elt) { return hb_ctz (v: elt); }
320 static unsigned int elt_get_max (const elt_t &elt) { return hb_bit_storage (v: elt) - 1; }
321
322 typedef hb_vector_size_t<elt_t, PAGE_BITS / 8> vector_t;
323
324 static constexpr unsigned ELT_BITS = sizeof (elt_t) * 8;
325 static constexpr unsigned ELT_MASK = ELT_BITS - 1;
326
327 static constexpr unsigned BITS = sizeof (vector_t) * 8;
328 static constexpr unsigned MASK = BITS - 1;
329 static_assert ((unsigned) PAGE_BITS == (unsigned) BITS, "");
330
331 elt_t &elt (hb_codepoint_t g) { return v[(g & MASK) / ELT_BITS]; }
332 const elt_t& elt (hb_codepoint_t g) const { return v[(g & MASK) / ELT_BITS]; }
333 static constexpr elt_t mask (hb_codepoint_t g) { return elt_t (1) << (g & ELT_MASK); }
334
335 vector_t v;
336};
337static_assert (hb_bit_page_t::PAGE_BITS == sizeof (hb_bit_page_t) * 8, "");
338

340#endif /* HB_BIT_PAGE_HH */
